nd some even do it for them. Parents like to think that their kids are so bright that they go on to the next level in each class. Some claim their kids have gone through everything and are ready to graduate from high school at ten years old. Many home schooled students that are put back into a public school are often two years behind other students. Until home schooled students go to school and take mid-term and final exams, it is a joke. I dare any home schooled students to go to a regular school and take a final exam. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="833" language="en" documentId="158" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="hurleyvision" date="7/29/2013 10:43 PM GMT+0200" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.washingtonpost.com/local/students-home-schooling-highlights-debate-over-va-religious-exemption-law/2013/07/28/ee2dbb1a-efbc-11e2-bed3-b9b6fe264871_comment.html?commentID=washingtonpost.com/ffc21007-6dcb-415a-bced-827935478e91/" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="158" notes="" title="Student’s home-schooling highlights debate over Va. religious exemption law"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="833"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>